  [Great views but some small issues](https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g60724-d550110-r814941140-Coyote_Cabin_Rentals-Moab_Utah.html)
  
  We loved the location and the amazing view (see photos). It is about a 30 minute drive from Moab however. Kitchen was good to go. The small issues were:
  
  .
  
  1\. WIFI: No real WiFi and very poor cell service in our Pioneer 2. Ask for Pioneer 1 if WiFi is important to you.
  
  .
  
  2\. SPIDERS: There were these nuisance spiders around. Not overwhelming, but you would see them, mainly in the bathroom and run into webs from time to time.
  
  .
  
  3\. NO FIREPLACE: They have a fire pit but it would be nicer to have a fireplace inside. One day it was cold rained the whole day and we were stuck inside.
  
  .
  
  4\. COWS: Again they were hanging around our car from time to time. Your call here.
  
  .
  
  5\. UPSTAIRS KING BED: The bath was on the first floor but the king bed on the second. We stayed in the first floor bedroom with the queen.
  
